	<td class="alt1">
	
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div><br /> ok after some deep thought (My blonde brain hurts),  I think I am ready to proclaim how I think specialization works given VI history with formula and numbers (they really do try to keep the formulas simple)<br />
<br />
disclaimer....<br />
THIS IS JUST MY OPINION AND HAS NOT BEEN CONFIRMED BY VI. I DERIVED THIS PURELY FROM OUR TESTING AND SHOULD NOT BE TAKEN AS GOSPEL.<br />
<br />
ok.<br />
----------------------------------------------------------<br />
Specialization is a random roll that gives you the possibility of a 50% mana reduction in the cost of the spell. <br />
<br />
A specialization of 200 gives you a 20% chance of reducing a spells mana cost by 50% (thus a 10% overall gain on average)<br />
<br />
A specialization of 50 gives you a 5% chance of reducing a spells mana cost by 50% (thus a 2.5% overall gain on average)<br />
<br />
--Spell Casting Mastery 1 increases this chance by 5% so you have an additional 5% chance of reducing a spells mana cost by 50% (thus an additional 2.5% overall gain on average)<br />
<br />
--Spell Casting Mastery 2 increases this chance by 15% so you have an additional 15% chance of reducing a spells mana cost by 50% (thus an additional 7.5% overall gain on average)<br />
<br />
--Spell Casting Mastery 3 increases this chance by 30% so you have an additional 30% chance of reducing a spells mana cost by 50% (thus an additional 15% overall gain on average)<br />
<br />
<br />
Thus a person with Spell Casting Mastery 2 casting their 200 specialization would have a 20% chance (200 spec) PLUS a 15% chance (SCM2) for a total of a 35% chance of reducing their mana by 50% on a spell. This would be an average overall gain of 17.5%.<br />
<br />
The same person in their 50 spec would have a (5% PLUS 15%) 20% chance on their lower specced spells. This would be an average overall gain of 10%.<br />
<br />
Mik's numbers and my numbers support this conclusion. I think that This has convinced me that SCM is the single most improvement of all the AA abilities as SCM3 should provide (just itself) an additional 15% gain in all casting.<br />
<br />
A person with SCM 3 should have a 20% chance (200 spec) PLUS a 30% chance (SCM3) total of 50% chance of a 50% mana reduction on spells for an overall gain of 25% !!!!<br />
---------------------------------------------------------<br />
<br />
Whew. Good work Mik and I would like to thank you for this. I feel pretty confident in how specialization works now and it is due entirely to your hard work. Those tests are awful boring to run <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Smilie" class="inlineimg" /> <br />
<br />
Good Luck to everyone and I hope this sheds some light on Specialization. Anyone with SCM 1 or 3 feel free to test and let us know if it fell within these parameters.<br />
<br />
/hugs<br />
<br />
Fasty<br />
 <br /></div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
